font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">However, other</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> recommendations are relevant</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">; the Committee is currently conducting an inquiry into the scrutiny process, and as part of this inquiry has been reviewing both its own ways of working and its relationship with Departmental Select Committees.  Our Report is currently under preparation but we set out below some initiatives we have already taken which are relevant </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">to the Liaison Committee Report</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.  The inquiry has enabled the Committee to have an internal discussion about its objectives and purpose, and test our initial views with academics, other Members of the House and parliamentarians throughout the EU.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Public engagement: meeting summaries and the media</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Liaison Committee </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">eport stresses the importance of wider public and stakeholder engagement.  From the beginning of the 2013-14 Session the Scrutiny Committee has agreed a weekly summary of its decisions, which is published with its Report but is also - crucially - emailed to an increasing distribution list shortly after the meeting, as well as being placed on the Committee</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s website.  This initiative means that the Committee now has a means of explaining the reasoning for its decisions within hours of the meeting, and has received excellent feedback.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">We have liaised with the House of Commons outreach service to put on a highly successful event on the scrutiny system in conjunction with King</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s College London. A further event is planned for the new year.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Part of the Committee’s scrutiny inquiry is an examination of how its work is covered by the media.  It is our view that there has been a comparative lack of coverage to date of this type of legislative scrutiny. Unfortunately one key witness, the Chairman of the BBC Trust (Lord Patten) has recently </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">twice </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">refused to appear before the Committee to give oral evidence.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Joint working</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Scrutiny Committee has been examining how its links with Departmental Select Committees can be improved.  Much has already been done in this area: at staf</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">f level the network of Committee ‘c</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ontact points</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> has been re-established (with the assistance of the National Parliament Office), more Opinions have been requested and the response rate has increased.  Our recent work with the Home Affairs and Justice Committees on the 2014 </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">block </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">opt-out was an excellent example of co-operation </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">between select committees. We are examining how Departmental Select Committees could have greater access to the useful briefings produced by the National Parliament Office, particularly the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Brussels Bulletin</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Further analysis and recommendations on these important issues will be included in the forthcoming scrutiny </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">eport.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Core tasks</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Committee welcomes the new core task set by the Liaison Committee relating to European scrutiny.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Pre-appointment hearings</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Committee has sought to hold an oral evidence session with the incoming Head of the</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> UK</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> Permanent Representation to the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">EU</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, Ivan Rogers.  This </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">appointment </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">has also been the subject of correspondence between the Foreign Affairs Committee and the FCO.  We remain of the view that this is a quasi-legislative post, and should be subject to a pre-appointment hearing.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Engagement with other institutions</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Committee actively engages with and scrutinises the European institutions through participation in international fora such as COSAC. We </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">hold</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> regular meetings with the House of Lords EU Committee, our equivalent Committees in the Scottish Parliament, Northern Ireland Assembly and National Assembly for Wales and UK MEPs.  We administer the ESID database on behalf of both Houses of Parliament.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">We have actively engaged with the Government to improve the guidance given to civil servants on the production of Explanatory Memoranda.  The Chair and Members have addressed meetings of civil servants to give them a first hand account of the work of the Committee.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Publications</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Since the beginning of the 2013-14 </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">S</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ession the Committee has been publishing much shorter report chapters for documents being considered for the second time and has changed the format of Committee papers to save paper.  As the Committee continues to consider its </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">scrutiny R</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">eport we will review our publications and wider ways of working, for example the scope to send papers to some Members in electronic form.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">We will also discuss the Liaison Committee's wider recommendations on the conduct of inquiries.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">6 November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>